title.narrative: Act to End Neglected Tropical Diseases | West

description.narrative: (USAID Global Health (GH)): &lt;!--br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--&gt;The purpose of Act to End Neglected Tropical Diseases (NTDs) | West is to support disease-endemic countries to control and/or eliminate NTDs with proven, cost-effective public health interventions. Building on the success USAID has achieved through previous investments to expand national integrated NTD programs, this program will continue to support 11 countries in West Africa to advance towards elimination and to access and leverage the drug donations needed to control NTDs that cannot be eliminated with the currently available strategies and tools. This program will work with national control programs to implement activities, such as mass drug administration, to control and/or eliminate NTDs and build capacity for controlling NTDs that cannot be eliminated.
